reason.tex:
\begin{align}
\frac{d}{dx}A^2 &= \underbrace{-4\cdot(x+10)^2\cdot (x-5)}_{\text{from last step}} \\
\therefore \frac{dA^2}{dx^2} &= -4\underbrace{\left[ (x+10)^2 + 2\cdot(x+10)\cdot(x-5)\right] }_{\text{Chain Rule}}\\
&= -4\cdot(x+10)^2\left[ (x+10)+2\cdot(x-5)\right] \\
&= -12\cdot (x+10)^2\cdot x \\
&\therefore \left[\frac{dA^2}{dx^2}\right]_{x=5} \lt 0 \implies\text{ maxima }\\
&\text{And, }A_{max} = \left[ (10+x)\cdot \sqrt{100-x^2}\right]_{x=5} \\
&= 15\cdot\sqrt{100-25} = 15\sqrt{75} \\
&= 15\sqrt{25\times 3} = 75\sqrt{3}\text{ sq. units}
\end{align}
